The extra code I "borrowed" from here: https://github.com/MozillaSecurity/libfuzzer-python-bridge . It basically spins up python and then calls the fuzzing method from C code. Then after that I had to use this custom version of the rusts libfuzzer to fuzz librsvg. Simple eh? 🙃 I wish there was a better way to do this. Regular afl++ has a simple environment variable (see AFL_PYTHON_MODULE in https://aflplus.plus/docs/env_variables/) which you can use to enable python custom mutation, but cargo libfuzzer does not. I documented some of those steps in my blog bost. Here is then how I actually started fuzzing: https://personnumber3377.github.io/projects/improving_the_librsvg_stuff.html#starting-fuzzing .
